[ ] enforce round-trip fidelity at the text boundary $ rescoped per DECISIONS.md 33: the contract is not "test every field" — types and tree-structure already own model validity. it is that three hand-maintained artifacts (formatter, tree-sitter grammar, Topiary query) agree on one wire protocol. a full proptest generator over arbitrary ActionLists is over-scoped; the real residue is reserved-char escaping, which is absent from all three layers today $ !1 +library,testing #019f26de-17cd-76f5-9f90-9d892741e8b8
    >[x] make the parser collect repeated context nodes $ the multi-tag data loss (2026-07-02): parser assigned per context node, keeping only the last space-separated tag. now extends. red→green regression test in parser.rs; closes cli bug 019f268f-eb4e; comma form ruled canonical $ +library %2026-07-03T00:00#019f26de-17cf-7e05-9d21-3bb62fa006e5
    >[x] implement reserved-char escaping (grammar, parser, formatter) with its round-trip tests $ the one genuine artifact-agreement residue. DONE 2026-07-03: safe_text (name, story/charter, predecessor) and description_text now accept \-escape sequences in the grammar; escape_field on write (link-aware — [[link]] spans copied verbatim), unescape_field on read; round-trip tests assert reserved sigils survive the formatter→Topiary→parser trip. deferred edges: context tag escaping and literal single brackets in names, both minor. this was the real !1 work the proptest generator was a proxy for $ +library,cli %2026-07-03T00:00#019f26de-17d0-739e-a4ae-42126d9e49a0
    >[ ] fuzz the tree-sitter grammar against the relaxed parser $ generated malformed input must never panic and recover-mode must never silently drop a parseable action — the relaxed-parser strict-linter decision only holds if recovery is total. the multi-tag fix above is one instance of recovery-totality; this generalizes it $ +library #019f26de-17d1-7491-8616-c8c3e8e575df
    >[ ] lint unescaped reserved sigils in freeform fields $ Decision 33 ruling 2 makes an unescaped reserved char a lint warning, never a parse error — the rule does not exist yet, and doctor's first run proved the gap: dependency-hygiene carried five syntax errors from names containing hash, at-sign, and bracket sigils, degrading every load until hand-escaped 2026-07-04. W-code in core lint.rs that suggests the escaped form $ +library #019f2ec3-df5f-7095-bb03-4b9d61dd7a62
[ ] add clearhead undo backed by git snapshots $ destructive commands rewrite truth immediately and fuzzy matching can pick the wrong target — wrong action plus no undo is the trust-destroying event. files-as-truth gets a time machine for free; leverage git rather than building one $ !1 +cli #019f26de-17d2-7edc-9578-b5bc873dc1f5
    >[ ] decide the snapshot mechanism and record it $ auto-commit to a workspace-local repo vs a hidden ledger repo vs reusing an existing repo when the workspace is already tracked; also whether snapshots batch or land per-mutation. note the layer split with platform-model: git snapshots are mechanism-level undo (restore files); the platform_model_undo_matrix action owns semantic undo theory — this decision should acknowledge both without blocking on the theory. record in DECISIONS.md $ +cli #019f26de-17d4-7580-91d1-5ebadc129a41
    >[ ] snapshot before every mutating command $ one integration point — the same choke point core-seam routes writes through; if snapshotting needs its own seam that is evidence for the write-path unification, not against it $ +cli <019f268f-eb33-7c70-b9e2-d79f46223f3d #019f26de-17d5-7c03-8f15-035f32a59cd6
    >[ ] add the undo command $ restore the workspace to the pre-mutation snapshot, print what changed; redo can wait for demand $ +cli #019f26de-17d7-7c79-add2-815b8c365ea5
[x] add clearhead doctor as a read-only workspace fsck $ cross-file invariants have accumulated with no holistic check — transparency applied to the system itself. read-only always; fixing stays with the commands that own each file. DONE 2026-07-04: first run on the platform workspace immediately found real debt — a charter file parsing with 5 errors from unescaped reserved sigils, four orphaned sidecars from archived charters, and five stale sidecar entries — the emergence the charter predicted $ !2 +cli,library %2026-07-04T00:00#019f26de-17d8-7068-b861-a6ed06e2dfb6
    >[x] inventory the invariants as the check list $ DONE 2026-07-04, recorded in DECISIONS.md 34: load integrity, duplicate UUIDs within and across files, dangling predecessors and unresolvable charter parent aliases, alias collisions, sidecar coherence including source_vevent pointing at absent VEVENTs, plans directories matching no charter, and durability residue. survey found two gaps the old list missed: one corrupt sidecar hard-fails the entire workspace load, and load invents implicit charters for unmatched plans directories instead of reporting. new checks fold in as dogfooding finds them $ +library %2026-07-04T00:00#019f26de-17da-7e15-9e0b-e4936b9a5db7
    >[x] split read_workspace out of load_workspace $ per DECISIONS.md 34: a pure fault-tolerant reader that never mutates and never refuses — per-file failures become findings data alongside whatever loaded. DONE 2026-07-04: read_workspace returns WorkspaceRead with charters plus Finding records; corrupt sidecars, unparseable files, and bad ics now degrade to findings instead of aborting the whole load, verified old-vs-new at the CLI. load_workspace is recover_pending plus read plus warning display. dogfooding note: read actions without a charter filter bypasses the loader entirely — core-seam evidence $ +library %2026-07-04T00:00#019f2e8e-8855-77e1-a4c2-37f126babb96
